			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Business Analyst/ Quality Assurance Contractor</strong></p>
<p>
The Business Analyst/ Quality Assurance is a member of the CRUX (Content, Requirements and User Experience) team whose primary responsibility is to elicit, analyze, validate, specify and manage the real needs of the project stakeholders. The Business Analyst/ QA provides leadership in defining business and functional requirements and coordinating large, complex business projects and/or tasks. Business Analysts must be excellent communicators, tactful diplomats, problem solvers, and thinkers and analyzers - with the ability to understand and respond to user needs in a flexible development environment.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Gather and document business needs from client stakeholders.</li>
<li>
Interview stakeholders, conduct site visits, manage JAD sessions, conduct surveys, as needed. Must be equally at ease interviewing very technical and very non-technical stakeholders.</li>
<li>
Analyze business and user needs, and translate them into proper system requirement specifications.</li>
<li>
Write and execute thorough use cases, being sure to align with wireframes created by the User Experience group.</li>
<li>
Work with a User Experience Architect to ensure proper translation of business requirements into an effective interface design.</li>
<li>
Be the &quot;go to&quot; person when the production team has questions/issues.</li>
<li>
Represent requirements using alternative methods, such as analysis diagrams, prototypes or scenarios, where appropriate.</li>
<li>
Manage requirements traceability information and track requirements status throughout the project.</li>
<li>
Establish and implement effective requirements practices, including use and continuous improvement of a requirements process. Assist with the development of the organization&rsquo;s requirements policies, procedures, and tools.</li>
<li>
Create test cases and test plans.</li>
<li>
Ability to create, manage, and track defects.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Knowledge Skills &amp; Abilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
An understanding of contemporary requirements elicitation, analysis and verification practices and the ability to apply them in practice.</li>
<li>
Interpersonal skills, to help negotiate priorities and deadlines and to resolve conflict among project stakeholders.</li>
<li>
Strong comfort level with technology and technological processes and principles; the successful candidate must be able to converse comfortably with development stakeholders and understand enough to see risks and ask appropriate follow-on questions.</li>
<li>
Experience with dynamic web-based applications.</li>
<li>
Exposure to Marketing field, particularly web and interactive Marketing.</li>
<li>
Highly motivated and focused personality who can facilitate and lead requirements workshops and JAD sessions.</li>
<li>
Organizational skills to work with a vast array of information gathered during elicitation and analysis and to cope with rapidly changing information.</li>
<li>
Proficient in handling multiple projects for multiple Project Managers.</li>
<li>
Ability to think on both a broad and detailed level.</li>
<li>
Interest and abilities in any of the following areas are considered a plus: Research, Content Strategy, Information Architecture, Interactive Design, and Testing.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of SDLC.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Minimum Education/Experience Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelors Degree or Equivalent experience in related field.</li>
<li>
At least 3 years of experience as a Business Analyst.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
